goals.visualization: line chart of Deaths over Year

goals.question: What is the relationship between the number of deaths and the year of the disaster?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of Deaths over Year
goals.rationale: This visualization can help identify if there is a correlation between the number of deaths and the year of the disaster.

code:
```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='Year')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['Year'], data['Deaths'], color='red', linewidth=2)
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Deaths')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of disaster-related deaths over time?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('Entity')['Deaths'].sum().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(data['Entity'], data['Deaths'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Disaster Type')
    ax.set_ylabel('Deaths')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of deaths across different types of disasters?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Entity'] = data['Entity'].astype('category')
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data['Deaths'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Deaths'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Deaths'])]
    data = data.groupby('Entity').mean().reset_index()
    plt.scatter(data['Entity'], data['Deaths'])
    plt.axhline(y=data['Deaths'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Average Deaths')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel('Disaster Type')
    plt.ylabel('Average Deaths per Disaster')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average number of deaths per disaster?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='Deaths', ascending=False)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax.axis('off')
    ax.axis('tight')
    ax.table(cellText=data.head(10).values, colLabels=data.columns, loc='center')
    plt.title('What is the most deadly disaster on record?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
